default1.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultResult
default&#xa0;
defaultCurrently, 
defaultEuropean
default electrical utilities are suffering.  Low profitability, following on from low fossil plant utilisation, and long term punitive gas contracts is the current European norm.  There is a strategic space for multinational utilities to take synergies from diffe
defaultring peak times and scarcities of fossil plant in some markets, while surpluses exist in others.  None of this can happen without Supergrid.  European trading 
defaultin electricity is minimal now. 
defaultWith Supergrid trading activity will ensure that, on a pan-Europea
defaultn scale, the electricity is produced from the lowest cost sources 
defaultreducing the overall price 
defaultto the consumer across the EU
default.
